<blockquote className="">{`
`}
<h5 className="">{`Caveat with anchors`}</h5>
{`
`}
<p className="">{`By default, browsers will treat all native form controls (`}
<code className="">{`<input>`}</code>
{`, `}
<code className="">{`<select>`}</code>
{` and `}
<code className="">{`<button>`}</code>
{` elements)
inside a `}
<code className="">{`<fieldset disabled>`}</code>
{` as disabled, preventing both keyboard and mouse interactions on them.
However, if your form also includes `}
<code className="">{`<Button href="" />`}</code>
{` components, these will only be given a style of `}
<code className="">{`pointer-events: none`}</code>
{`.
As noted in the section about `}
<a href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.5/components/buttons/#disabled-state" className="">{`disabled state for buttons`}</a>
{` (and specifically in the sub-section for anchor elements),
this CSS property won’t prevent keyboard users from being able to focus or activate these links.
So to be safe, use custom JavaScript to disable such links.`}</p>
{`
`}</blockquote>
{`
`}
<blockquote className="">{`
`}
<h5 className="">{`Cross-browser compatibility`}</h5>
{`
`}
<p className="">{`While BootCell will apply these styles in all browsers, Internet Explorer 11 don’t fully support the `}
<code className="">{`disabled`}</code>
{` property on a `}
<code className="">{`<fieldset>`}</code>
{`.
Use custom JavaScript to disable the fieldset in these browsers.`}</p>
{`
`}</blockquote>
{`
`}
<h2 className="">{`Validation`}</h2>
{`
`}
<p className="">{`Provide valuable, actionable feedback to your users with HTML5 form validation `}
<a href="https://caniuse.com/#feat=form-validation" className="">{`available in all our supported browsers`}</a>
{`.
Choose from the browser default validation feedback, or implement custom messages with our built-in classes and starter JavaScript.`}</p>
{`
`}
<blockquote className="">{`
`}
<p className="">{`We are aware that currently the client-side custom validation styles and tooltips are not accessible,
since they are not exposed to assistive technologies. While we work on a solution,
we’d recommend using the default browser validation method.`}</p>
{`
`}</blockquote>
{`
`}
<h3 className="">{`How it works`}</h3>
{`
`}
<p className="">{`Here’s how form validation works with BootCell:`}</p>
{`
`}
<ul className="">{`
`}
<li className="">{`
`}
<p className="">{`HTML form validation is applied via CSS’s two pseudo-classes, `}
<code className="">{`:invalid`}</code>
{` and `}
<code className="">{`:valid`}</code>
{`. It applies to `}
<code className="">{`<input>`}</code>
{`, `}
<code className="">{`<select>`}</code>
{`, and `}
<code className="">{`<textarea>`}</code>
{` elements.`}</p>
{`
`}</li>
{`
`}
<li className="">{`
`}
<p className="">{`BootCell scopes the `}
<code className="">{`:invalid`}</code>
{` and `}
<code className="">{`:valid`}</code>
{` styles to `}
<code className="">{`<Form validated />`}</code>
{`. Otherwise, any required field without a value shows up as invalid on page load. This way, you may choose when to activate them (typically after form submission is attempted).`}</p>
{`
`}</li>
{`
`}
<li className="">{`
`}
<p className="">{`To reset the appearance of the form (for instance, in the case of dynamic form submissions using AJAX), remove the `}
<code className="">{`validated`}</code>
{` property from the `}
<code className="">{`<Form />`}</code>
{` again after submission.`}</p>
{`
`}</li>
{`
`}
<li className="">{`
`}
<p className="">{`As a fallback, `}
<code className="">{`valid`}</code>
{` property may be used instead of the pseudo-classes for `}
<a href="#Server-side" className="">{`server side validation`}</a>
{`. It doesn't require a `}
<code className="">{`validated`}</code>
{` property on `}
<code className="">{`<Form />`}</code>
{`.`}</p>
{`
`}</li>
{`
`}
<li className="">{`
`}
<p className="">{`Due to constraints in how CSS works, we cannot (at present) apply styles to a `}
<code className="">{`<label>`}</code>
{` that comes before a form control in the DOM without the help of custom JavaScript.`}</p>
{`
`}</li>
{`
`}
<li className="">{`
`}
<p className="">{`All modern browsers support the `}
<a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/sec-forms.html#the-constraint-validation-api" className="">{`constraint validation API`}</a>
{`, a series of JavaScript methods for validating form controls.`}</p>
{`
`}</li>
{`
`}
<li className="">{`
`}
<p className="">{`Feedback messages may utilize the `}
<a href="#Browser-defaults" className="">{`browser defaults`}</a>
{` (different for each browser, and unstylable via CSS) or our custom feedback styles with additional HTML and CSS.`}</p>
{`
`}</li>
{`
`}
<li className="">{`
`}
<p className="">{`You may provide custom validity messages with `}
<code className="">{`setCustomValidity`}</code>
{` in JavaScript.`}</p>
{`
`}</li>
{`
`}</ul>
{`
`}
<p className="">{`With that in mind, consider the following demos for our custom form validation styles, optional server side properties, and browser defaults.`}</p>
{`
`}
<h3 className="">{`Custom styles`}</h3>
{`
`}
<p className="">{`For custom BootCell form validation messages, you’ll need to add the `}
<code className="">{`validate`}</code>
{` boolean property to your `}
<code className="">{`<Form />`}</code>
{`.
This disables the browser default feedback tooltips, but still provides access to the form validation APIs in JavaScript.
Try to submit the form below; our JavaScript will intercept the submit button and relay feedback to you.
When attempting to submit, you’ll see the `}
<code className="">{`:invalid`}</code>
{` and `}
<code className="">{`:valid`}</code>
{` styles applied to your form controls.`}</p>
{`
`}
<p className="">{`Custom feedback styles apply custom colors, borders, focus styles, and background icons to better communicate feedback.`}</p>
{`
`}
<Example>
    <Form validate>
        <div className="form-row">
            <FormField
                className="col-md-6 mb-3"
                label="First name"
                value="Mark"
                required
                validMessage="Looks good!"
            />
            <FormField
                className="col-md-6 mb-3"
                label="Last name"
                value="Otto"
                required
                validMessage="Looks good!"
            />
        </div>
        <div className="form-row">
            <FormField
                className="col-md-6 mb-3"
                label="City"
                required
                invalidMessage="Please provide a valid city."
            />
            <FormField
                className="col-md-3 mb-3"
                is="select"
                label="State"
                required
                invalidMessage="Please select a valid state."
            >
                <option selected disabled value="">
                    Choose...
                </option>
                <option>...</option>
            </FormField>
            <FormField
                className="col-md-3 mb-3"
                label="Zip"
                required
                invalidMessage="Please provide a valid zip."
            />
        </div>
        <ToggleField
            className="mb-3"
            type="checkbox"
            required
            invalidMessage="You must agree before submitting."
        >
            Agree to terms and conditions
        </ToggleField>
        <Button type="submit" color="primary">
            Submit form
        </Button>
    </Form>
</Example>
{`
`}
